***************************** T A L Y S **************************8228 1451
                                                                  8228 1451
TALYS is a computer code system for the prediction and analysis   8228 1451
of nuclear reactions. TALYS simulates reactions that involve      8228 1451
neutrons, gamma-rays, protons, deuterons, tritons, helions and    8228 1451
alpha-particles, in the 1 keV - 200 MeV energy range. This is     8228 1451
achieved by implementing a suite of nuclear reaction models into  8228 1451
a single code system. This nuclear data file is based on a        8228 1451
theoretical analysis that utilizes the optical model, compound    8228 1451
nucleus statistical theory, fission, direct reactions and         8228 1451
pre-equilibrium processes, in combination with databases and      8228 1451
models for nuclear structure. The following output of TALYS is    8228 1451
stored in this data file:                                         8228 1451
                                                                  8228 1451
- Total, elastic and non-elastic cross sections                   8228 1451
- Inelastic cross sections to discrete states                     8228 1451
- Exclusive channel cross sections, e.g. (n,g), (n,2n), (n,np),.. 8228 1451
- Inelastic scattering angular distributions to discrete states   8228 1451
- Exclusive channel energy spectra                                8228 1451
- Exclusive channel double-differential spectra                   8228 1451
- Exclusive gamma production for discrete states and continuum    8228 1451
- Elastic scattering angular distributions                        8228 1451
- Recoil data                                                     8228 1451
- Total particle cross sections, e.g. (n,xn), (n,xp),..           8228 1451
- Total particle energy spectra                                   8228 1451
- Total particle double-differential spectra                      8228 1451
- Isomeric and ground state cross sections                        8228 1451
- Residual production cross sections                              8228 1451
                                                                  8228 1451
For a description of the used nuclear models and their            8228 1451
parameterization we refer to [kon12]. If for this specific        8228 1451
nuclide we deviate from the global parameterization, it is made   8228 1451
explicit above under Nuclide Specific Information.                8228 1451
